It's been a decade since the South District in New York last processed a death penalty case.
The defendant, Khalid Barnes, was found guilty of murdering two drug traffickers, but was finally sentenced to life imprisonment in September 2009.
The last time a death penalty was executed in a federal case in New York was in Julius and Ethel Rosenberg in 1953. This marriage was executed after they were sentenced by conspiracy to commit espionage for the Soviet Union during the Cold War two years earlier.
